    <entry xml:lang="en">
        <title>Refactoring with AST-Grep</title>
        <published>2026-02-23T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2026-02-23T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        
        <author>
          <name>
            
              Willem Vanhulle
            
          </name>
        </author>
        
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://sysghent.be/events/refactoring/"/>
        <id>https://sysghent.be/events/refactoring/</id>
        
        <content type="html" xml:base="https://sysghent.be/events/refactoring/">&lt;p&gt;Recent advancements in industry made refactoring incredibly boring, expensive and slow. (&lt;em&gt;Think about the sound a donkey makes but then reversed.&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;)&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;willemvanhulle.tech&quot;&gt;Willem Vanhulle&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; will show how to make refactoring great again with a tool &lt;a rel=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;ast-grep.github.io&#x2F;&quot;&gt;AST-Grep&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;. This tool can be used to apply extremely targeted and efficient refactors to large codebases in milliseconds.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A sample from the official website:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;ast-grep -p &amp;#39;$A &amp;amp;&amp;amp; $A()&amp;#39; -r &amp;#39;$A?.()&amp;#39;
&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The presentation (of 30 minutes.) will not be too technical, so people are able to follow along after a long workday without having a laptop in front of them.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Afterward, let’s have a drink in the area!&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</content>
        
