        <title>NuShell: Superglue for your Operating System</title>
        <published>2025-12-03T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2025-12-03T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        
        <author>
          <name>
            
              Willem Vanhulle
            
          </name>
        </author>
        
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://sysghent.be/events/nushell/"/>
        <id>https://sysghent.be/events/nushell/</id>
        
        <content type="html" xml:base="https://sysghent.be/events/nushell/">&lt;p&gt;(Presented by &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;sysghent.be&#x2F;events&#x2F;nushell&#x2F;willemvanhulle.tech&quot;&gt;Willem Vanhulle&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;.)&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;sysghent.be&#x2F;events&#x2F;nushell&#x2F;nushell.sh&quot;&gt;NuShell&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; is a fairly new type of shell focused on &lt;em&gt;functional structured data processing&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;. It &lt;strong&gt;fixes most problems of the traditional POSIX shellls&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; and takes inspiration from PowerShell and real programming languages.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Willem has been a daily user of Nu shell for almost a year and would like to share with you how it can improve your efficiency as a script user, scientist, engineer or developer. Nu shell allows you to process all kinds of data in clean pipelines and build easy to maintain scripts.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The plan for this evening is:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;19:30: interactive presentation about nu&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20:30: practice session&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can find more information about the language at &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;sysghent.be&#x2F;events&#x2F;nushell&#x2F;nushell.sh&quot;&gt;nushell.sh&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;. Recently, Willem also released a linter for Nu to help you get started: &lt;a rel=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;wvhulle&#x2F;nu-lint&quot;&gt;nu-lint&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</content>
        
